---
description: Delete unused code only with evidence it’s safe
alwaysApply: true
---

# Dead code

- Delete only with **evidence**: build, tests, linter unused, obvious orphans.
- Remove unused helpers, imports, stale branches, stale comments—not ambiguous dynamic refs without proof.
- Never delete `node_modules`, `.git`, secrets, or unknown-purpose files.
- After deletion: touched area must still build/test at least as before.
